<HEADLINE>
FT  12 NOV 94 / International Company News: BHP in venture with US group
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The steel division of Broken Hill Proprietary, the Australian resources
group, and North Star Steel, part of the privately-owned Cargill group in
the US, are joining forces to build and operate a new steel mini-mill in the
US Midwest at a cost of around USDollars 400m, writes Nikki Tait in Sydney.
The two companies will have 50-50 interests in the venture.
</TEXT>
